parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The expansion of the polyamide PA6 fuel tank can cause the tank to become misaligned with the frame, leading to interference with the steering and suspension, and potentially causing a fire due to the proximity of the tank to the exhaust system and rear wheel. Additionally, the expansion can cause the tank to leak fuel, leading to a hazardous situation.
symptoms: the tank does not sit correctly in the frame
the handlebar switch hits the tank when turned to the right
the front suspension fork tube hits the tank when steered to the left
the tank becomes nearly impossible to remove for routine maintenance
the front and rear bodywork panels become damaged at their attachment points
gas drips onto the back tire
and the house and garage smell of gasoline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The expansion of the fuel tank due to ethanol can cause the tank to swell, leading to misalignment of the vehicle's body, inhibited steering, and affected seating, which can compromise vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: The fuel tank is visibly swollen or bulging
the steering is difficult or unresponsive
the seating is uneven or uncomfortable.
